{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566889","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566889"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:50:53+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:50:53+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18902"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18902","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18902"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.81,0.1,0.08,0,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11635"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80132"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11635","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11635"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18902"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65409"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"17"},{"type":"tags","id":"18"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11348"},{"type":"tags","id":"11349"},{"type":"tags","id":"11350"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"},{"type":"tags","id":"12918"},{"type":"tags","id":"12921"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27371"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27372"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80132","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80132"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 42-year-old woman requires surgery for a symptomatic gallstone. The surgeon meets with her to discuss the procedure and obtain informed consent.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes a requirement for valid informed consent?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Patient must understand the nature and risks of the procedure","Patient must sign a written consent form","Consent must be obtained by the operating surgeon","Family members must be present during the discussion","Patient must be given 24 hours to make a decision"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe essential requirement for valid informed consent is that the \u003Cstrong\u003Epatient must understand the nature and risks of the procedure\u003C/strong\u003E. This understanding should include the purpose, significant risks, expected benefits, and reasonable alternatives to the proposed treatment.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPatient must sign a written consent form\u003C/strong\u003E - While documentation is important, valid consent can be given verbally for many procedures. A patient can also sign written consent without fully understanding the procedure.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFamily members must be present during the discussion\u003C/strong\u003E - While family involvement may be helpful, it is not required if the patient has capacity\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EConsent must be obtained by the operating surgeon\u003C/strong\u003E - Any qualified healthcare provider with adequate knowledge of the procedure can obtain consent\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPatient must be given 24 hours to make a decision\u003C/strong\u003E - While patients should not be rushed, there is no mandatory minimum time period\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EValid informed consent requires three key elements: the patient must have capacity to make the decision, receive adequate information about the procedure, and make the decision voluntarily without coercion.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Valid informed consent requires the patient to have capacity, receive adequate information, and make a voluntary decision without coercion.","Medical procedures cannot be performed without valid informed consent except in emergencies where the patient lacks capacity.","Information provided must include the nature of the procedure, significant risks, benefits, and reasonable alternatives."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx","Shah P, Thornton I, Kopitnik NL, Hipskind JE. Informed Consent. 2024 Nov 24. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2025 Jan\u2013. PMID: 28613577. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28613577/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65409"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18902"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65409","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65409"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-17T17:51:04+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-18T00:15:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11635"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80132"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"17","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/17"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude07","name":"Bioethics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"18","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/18"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddd1\u200d\u2696\ufe0f","name":"Medicolegal"